description: In "The Ticket," Aggie learns just how far she'll go for literary fame, and a boy who could be special enters the edges of Penny's life. And in "Weights," we get the slightest peek into the background of Aggie's mysterious crush.

In "Crush'd," first love hits Aggie with all the sweetness and gentleness of a Mack truck. And in "The Last Days of Summer," the end of summer break brings big changes not only to Penny and Aggie, but to Aggie's father and Penny's closest friend. One finds freedom, one finds a purpose, one finds loss, and one finds love.

description: Uniques: a group of people still hated and despised, unless they can be used. If you're different, dangerous even, what would you choose. Be locked up for life in fear you could and will hurt those around you or sign your life off to your country to do something noble.
name: Around the World

description: The war is over but not for everyone. Uniques still have to fight to be seen and to be heard if, in fact, they are heard at all. Society ignores them but they refuse to be ignored. Mentor, Kinetic and Current: three heroes the world over but are they enough to bring the conflict to an end?
name: At the Scene of Freedom

description: Uniques have won their rights. Children can live without fear of being institutionalized. A new dawn is being for the Uniques: a world without fear, a world with a future.
name: A New Begining

description:
More lies! More vampires! More puppets! Pinocchio is back, but now he must share the vampire-killing stage with his wooden siblings. The stakes are raised in this sequel to the acclaimed graphic novel, as Pinocchio unravels the mystery of the undead menace and his own shadowy background. But will turmoil within the band of slayers spoil their efforts as they battle the bloodsuckers across Italy and even at sea in this darkly funny take on the classic character?

Back Blurb

Pinocchio is back, continuing his quest to rid the world of vampires. Still haunted by Geppetto's death and in an uneasy alliance with an undead friend, Pinocchio is in danger of letting his anger consume him.

Fortunately, the actors of the Great Puppet Theater arrive on the scene to aid their brother-in-wood. Soon, they're journeying across Italy to the sea in a high-stakes pursuit of the source of the vampire scourge.
name: Pinocchio: Vampire Slayer and the Great Puppet Theater

description: Zemo and Bucky - two characters linked through history whether they like it or not. And now Zemo has set his sights on Bucky and plans to destroy our new Captain America one step at a time. It's the hardest hitting Captain America story ever by the awesome team of Ed Brubaker and Butch Guice. Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA #606-610.
name: Captain America: No Escape

description: A hero for the ages in a trio of war-torn tales! In Operation Zero Point, a squadron of anti-gravity Nazi aircraft rises from behind enemy lines! In Prisoners of Duty, Steve Rogers is taken captive along with fellow infantrymen inside the forbidding walls of a Nazi-held castle. And in America First!, the Commie-busting Cap of the '50s uncovers a fifth-columnist plot that has its origins in the most unsuspecting of places! It's Cap action set in war-torn Europe and at the height of America's Cold War with the Soviet Union, rendered by a contemporary crew of comics' best! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA: AMERICA FIRST, OPERATION ZERO POINT and PRISONERS OF DUTY.
name: Captain America: America First

description: Everyone's favorite Merc with a Mouth continues hacking and wisecracking his way across the Marvel Universe in this second volume of riotous, ridiculous and outright reprehensible team-ups! First up, Deadpool goes to England where he squares off with Captain Britain over a fabled weapons haul. Then, what happens when the only person a demonic sorceress named Satana can find to help her is our lovable and slightly deranged Deadpool? Well, telling you would be telling, but if you listen real hard you might hear the distant chimes of...wedding bells!? Also, Mr. X has traveled near and far and faced some of the best fighters the world has to offer. But can anything prepare him for what happens when Deadpol is contracted to kill him? Then Deadpool's destructive past catches up with him when he gets a call from the indestructible robot (and part-time insurance agent) Aaron Stack AKA Machine Man! All this plus GORILLA MAN! Collecting DEADPOOL TEAM-UP #893-889 and DEADPOOL CORPS: RANK AND FOUL.
name: Volume 2

Written by Geoff Johns, this tale of Gail Walker and her college students takes them through many of the monsters of Greek legend and myth. To restore things to normal they must return Pandora's Box to its rightful place.

This tale of Greek myth is a co-production of Humanoids & DC comics.
